Perhaps the simplest solution is to add _one_ event listener to the _parent element_ (cancionesA) instead and catch clicks from the child elements as they bubble up the DOM. This is known as [event delegation](https://davidwalsh.name/event-delegate). In your button loop you can assign an id to each button which you can then use to identify the button that was clicked.

